Prey: Flies, mosquitoes, crickets, moths and other small insects
Fun Fact: Green tree frogs breathe through their skin
Most Distinctive Feature: They’re amphibians, but they live in trees
Other Name(s): The Australian green tree frog is also known as White’s tree frog or dumpy tree frog
Location: Australia and North America Southeast Asia
Lifespan: With proper care, members of the Australian species can live 15 years in terrariums. The typical lifespan of the American species in captivity is six years.
Length: Members of the Australian species measure 4 inches long on average; members of the American species measure 2.5 inches long on average
Name: Green Tree Frog
